parameters: \c[22]Just so you know, you're about to face this dungeon's incredibly handsome, intelligent, \fiand\fi humble boss. If there's anything you'd like to do beforehand, do so now.
Would you like to return to the blue section of the dungeon?
You can't go back through the maze, so there's no point in returning from here.
Would you like to return to the green section of the dungeon?
Hm. Looks similar to a source crystal, but Alexander obviously wouldn't have the source crystal for the dungeon just hanging out in the hallway. Do you want to touch it?
You fill with energy, restoring up to 1000 health and 1 mana.
You fill with energy, restoring up to 1000 health.

\c[22]It just heals you, and if you're completely out of mana (and someone who uses mana), slightly restores your mana. As much as I love winning, bragging about beating unexhausted adventurer's doesn't stroke my ego hard enough.
The healing source crystal-thing is out of energy.

Hm. The passage behind you has abruptly shut. You double check by giving it a tap, but yeah, there's actually a wall there now, it's not just an illusion. Based on the carpet and walls, the other passages would also have led out here, but they too are blocked off. You can't sneak into those routes without the respective transformation or equipment, it seems.
